	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'm guessing that flicker can be mostly avoided in a homebrew fighting game by making each character roughly 32x64 pixels with 8x16 pixel sprites.</div>
<br />Unless when the characters kick, punch or release an attack, all of wich would exceed the 8 sprites limit.
<br />
<br />I'm more for using the background to draw one of the characters. Of course, you'd have to sacrifice a huge chunk of the backgroung, maybe only using a stripe way on top of the screen (where no character can jump) and below the character's feet. If you are really clever, you can still set a mood for the level even though there is no background behind the players.
<br />
<br />The good part is that you could also use the background color to draw the characters, so you have 4 colors for them instead of 3. It may not seem like much, but I think it makes a hell of a difference.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


