	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd do with smaller sprites. Why do we need so big sprites ? The inconvegnient of fighting game is that everything is about character graphics, but doing the characters the size they are in Double Dragon (I think it is 5x2 tiles) is okay. If you would kick or something it will never overpass 4 tiles wide per character. Maybe if they are lying on the ground it would be 5 tiles large, but it is rare that both characters are lying on the ground at the same time.
<br />If you'd go for big sprites, using one for BG is definitely necessary. Using one-screen mirroring with one name table for the background and status bar and the other for one of the characters may be pratical.
<br />The background in fighting games is mostly dummy (just here for ambiance), so basically having only BG on the top and the bottom of the fighting players would sure work well.
<br />Punch Out does the player and arbitral with BG, while all opponants are in sprites.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


